<problem display_name="Lecture 12 Problem 4: Data Security">
  <startouttext/>
  <p>If a site has a valid SSL certificate from a trusted CA, which of the following is true:<br/>
		i) The site is probably not "masquerading" as an impostor of a real site<br/>
		ii) CSRF + SQL injection are harder to mount against it<br/>
		iii) Your data is secure once it reaches the site</p>
  <endouttext/>
  <choiceresponse>
    <checkboxgroup>
      <choice correct="true">
        <text>
          <span style="color: #F90;">(i) only</span>
        </text>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="false">
        <text>
          <span style="color: #063;">(i) &amp; (ii) only</span>
        </text>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="false">
        <text>
          <span style="color: #C00;">(ii) &amp; (iii) only</span>
        </text>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="false">
        <text>
          <span style="color:#006;">(i), (ii) &amp; (iii)</span>
        </text>
      </choice>
    </checkboxgroup>
  </choiceresponse>
</problem>
